</tr></tbody></table><h2>Notes</h2>
<p>These notes relate to Widow Class B, C &amp; D Pension and BVA - July 1942 to September 1996:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Note</th>
<th scope="col">Explanation</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td id="NoteA">A</td>
<td>Class A widow's pension became payable to a woman whose husband had been imprisoned for at least 6 months and who had the custody, care and control of a child or children.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteB">B</td>
<td>The dates on which the rates became payable.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteC">C</td>
<td>Payments were made 4 weekly in arrears from this date.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteD">D</td>
<td>Payments were made fortnightly in arrears from this date.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteE">E</td>
<td>From 7 August 1968, widows' pensions were regarded as being paid in fortnightly instalments of one twenty-sixth of the annual rate rather than fortnightly in arrears. (Reference Secretary's instructions F174/103, C1707/45 of 7 August 1968.)</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteF">F</td>
<td>Maximum increase paid where means as assessed was less than $520.00. Amount of increase was reduced by half of means as assessed in excess of $520.00.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteG">G</td>
<td>WidB became payable at standard rate.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteH">H</td>
<td>From 11 December 1975 widow's pension paydays were amalgamated with <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#age" title="Age pension">Age</a> and invalid pension paydays. The last widow's pension and supporting mother's benefit payday was 2 December 1975.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteI">I</td>
<td>From 1 July 1987 progressive phasing out of WidB commenced. Only current cases or new claims where age and widowhood criteria were satisfied at 1 July 1987 were entitled to payments beyond that date.</td>
</tr><tr><td id="NoteJ">J</td>
<td>From 20 March 1998, pensions became benchmarked against 25 per cent of <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#mtawe" title="Male Total Average Weekly Earnings">MTAWE</a>, in addition to <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#cpi" title="Consumer price index">CPI</a> indexation.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2>Widow class C - Widowed Person's Allowance - BVA</h2>
<p>Definition of necessitous circumstances:</p>
<ul><li>Prior to 18 April 1967 net income of less than $7.00 per week and less than $400.00 in liquid assets (<a href="../guide-social-security-law/1/1/a/290">1.1.A.290</a>).</li>
<li>From 18 April 1967 net income of less than $10.00 per week and less than $400.00 in liquid assets.</li>
<li>From 25 November 1976 net income of less than $10.00 per week.</li>
<li>From 13 April 1984 net income of $30.00 per week or less.</li>
<li>From 21 March 1985 net income of $30.00 per week or less and readily available funds of $3,000 or less.</li>
<li>From 1 August 1985 net income of $30.00 per week or less and readily available funds of $5,000 or less.</li>
<li>From 1 January 1986 net income of $30.00 per week or less and readily available funds of $6,000 or less.</li>
<li>From 1 March 1989 Class C widow's pension was replaced by widowed person allowance and became subject to the normal income and assets test. It is payable to both men and women.</li>
<li>From 1994 Widowed person allowance was renamed BVA.</li>
</ul></article>	<div id="view-last-reviewed-date">
		
		  
